Yes, exactly. The cooldown is being applied unconditionally in the toolbar button's onClick, regardless of quest step.

The fix is simple — skip the cooldown if the quest requires rain:

tsx
if (def.id === 'rain') {
  const gs = gsRef.current;
  const questNeedsRain = gs.questStep === 'first_rain' || gs.questStep === 'second_rain';

  triggerRain(gs);

  if (!questNeedsRain) {
    setUI((p) => ({ ...p, rainCooling: true }));
    setTimeout(() => setUI((p) => ({ ...p, rainCooling: false })), 15000);
  }

  // rest of rain logic...
}
And the same guard on the rainCooling visual disable:

tsx
const rainBlocked = def.id === 'rain' && ui.rainCooling;
That line is already correct — it just needs rainCooling to never be set during quest rain steps, which the fix above handles.

So the cooldown kicks in normally during free_play and later, but during first_rain and second_rain the button stays active. One line of logic, no structural changes needed.

Found it! Look at **line 1956-1957**:

```ts
// Cap restoration at 89% if not all plant types or wildlife have been discovered
const missingPlants = getMissingPlants(gs);
```

There's a **cap at 89%** if you haven't discovered **all plant types**! Let me see the full logic:

