This is a classic mobile browser audio issue. The core problem is that mobile browsers (especially iOS Safari) block all audio until a user gesture triggers it. The Web Audio API context starts in a suspended state and won't resume automatically.
Here's what's almost certainly happening in your code:
The root cause: your audio context is being created on page load, but on mobile it stays suspended because no user gesture has explicitly resumed it yet. Desktop works because desktop browsers are more permissive.

Tell your agent this:

On mobile browsers, the Web Audio API requires explicit user gesture unlock before any sound can play. Add an audio unlock function that resumes the AudioContext on the first touch/click anywhere on the screen.

The fix has two parts:
Part 1 — Unlock the audio context on first touch:
ts// In your audio service or at the top of GameScene.tsx
let audioUnlocked = false;

function unlockAudio(audioCtx: AudioContext) {
  if (audioUnlocked) return;
  if (audioCtx.state === 'suspended') {
    audioCtx.resume().then(() => {
      audioUnlocked = true;
    });
  } else {
    audioUnlocked = true;
  }
}
Then in GameScene.tsx, add this to the outermost container div:
tsxonTouchStart={() => unlockAudio(yourAudioContext)}
onClick={() => unlockAudio(yourAudioContext)}
Part 2 — iOS Safari specific: iOS additionally requires a silent buffer to be played through the context before real sounds work. Add this inside unlockAudio:
ts// Play a silent buffer to fully unlock iOS
const buffer = audioCtx.createBuffer(1, 1, 22050);
const source = audioCtx.createBufferSource();
source.buffer = buffer;
source.connect(audioCtx.destination);
source.start(0);

Also check: if your footstep and rain sounds are created with new Audio() (HTML audio elements) rather than the Web Audio API, the fix is slightly different — you need to call .play() on a silent audio element on first touch instead. Can you tell me which approach your sound code uses — Web Audio API (AudioContext, createOscillator, createBufferSource) or HTML audio (new Audio('sound.mp3'))? That'll let me give you the exact patch.

Perfect, so the hints should be dynamic, condition-aware, and auto-dismiss once the animal appears. Here's the full getMossHint function covering all 13:
tsfunction getMossHint(gs: GameState): DialogueLine | null {
  if (gs.questStep !== 'free_play') return null;

  const restoration = calculateRestoration(gs);
  const bloomCount = countBlooming(gs);
  const plantDiversity = gs.discoveredPlants.size;
  const mulchCount = countTerrain(gs, 'mulch');
  const waterCount = countTerrain(gs, 'water');
  const avgFertility = getAvgFertility(gs);
  const discovered = gs.discoveredWildlife;

  // Check each animal in order of difficulty (easiest first)
  // so the most actionable hint shows first

  if (!discovered.includes('ant') && avgFertility < 20)
    return hint('The soil needs life in it first. 🐜 Ants follow fertility — mulch and moisture will bring them.');

  if (!discovered.includes('bee') && bloomCount < 1)
    return hint('Not a single flower is open. 🐝 Bees need something to visit — plant anything and let it bloom.');

  if (!discovered.includes('monarch') && !gs.discoveredPlants.has('milkweed'))
    return hint('There is a butterfly that will only come for one plant. 🦋 The Monarch follows milkweed — plant it and wait.');

  if (!discovered.includes('frog') && waterCount < 2)
    return hint('Something is missing from the edges of this place. 🐸 Frogs need water to return — the land needs at least two pools.');

  if (!discovered.includes('beetle') && (mulchCount < 2 || avgFertility < 25))
    return hint(`The ground needs more organic matter. 🪲 Beetles hide under mulch in fertile soil — you have ${mulchCount} mulch tile${mulchCount === 1 ? '' : 's'} so far.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('hoverfly') && bloomCount < 3)
    return hint(`${bloomCount} flower${bloomCount === 1 ? ' is' : 's are'} open. 🪰 Hoverflies need three blooms at once to find the valley.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('painted_lady') && (plantDiversity < 3 || bloomCount < 2))
    return hint(`You have ${plantDiversity} plant type${plantDiversity === 1 ? '' : 's'} and ${bloomCount} blooming. 🦋 The Painted Lady needs variety — three kinds of plants, two in bloom.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('dragonfly') && waterCount < 3)
    return hint(`${waterCount} water tile${waterCount === 1 ? '' : 's'} isn't enough. 🐛 Dragonflies patrol larger pools — the valley needs three.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('cottontail') && (bloomCount < 3 || plantDiversity < 3))
    return hint(`${bloomCount} blooms, ${plantDiversity} plant types. 🐇 Cottontail needs both — three blooms and three kinds of plants at once.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('finch') && plantDiversity < 4)
    return hint(`${plantDiversity} plant type${plantDiversity === 1 ? '' : 's'} so far. 🐦‍⬛ Finches need a diverse valley — try planting a fourth kind.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('quail') && restoration < 70)
    return hint(`The valley is ${Math.round(restoration)}% restored. 🐦 Quail return when the land reaches 70% — keep going.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('hawk') && restoration < 80)
    return hint(`${Math.round(restoration)}% restored. 🦅 The Hawk circles high — it waits for 80% before it lands.`);

  if (!discovered.includes('swallow') && (bloomCount < 5 || restoration < 85))
    return hint(`${bloomCount} flower${bloomCount === 1 ? '' : 's'} blooming, ${Math.round(restoration)}% restored. 🕊️ The Swallow counts every open bloom from above — it needs five at once and 85% restoration. Plant in waves so blooms overlap.`);

  return null;
}

function hint(text: string): DialogueLine {
  return { speaker: 'Moss', emoji: '💡', text };
}
A few things to note:
The hints are ordered easiest-first so the player always gets the most actionable next step, not an advanced hint when they haven't done basics yet. Once an animal is discovered its hint disappears permanently since we check !discovered.includes(...).
The swallow hint is the only one that gives explicit numbers for both conditions simultaneously — because by that point the player has earned the full picture.
